                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td bgcolor="#000000" height="8" width="100%" colspan="3"><span class="header">STCCG Puzzle Four: A Perplexing Paradox, a LooPHolE</span></td></tr><tr><td bgcolor="#333399" height="2" width="41%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="1%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="58%" bgcolor="#FF9C00"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td></tr></table><TABLE WIDTH="100%" CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN=2><SPAN CLASS="header">Rating </SPAN><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/rating/7.gif" BORDER=0></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=56"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=56"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=5866">Franklin "LooPHolE" Kenter</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Description</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%"><span class=text>Puzzles allow players to enhance their ablilities using their Stratgema, Vulcan Logic, and Klingon Honor.</span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Article</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%" ><span class=text>Since Puzzle Two has yet to be completely solved (as I keep updating misunderstood portions), it has been reposted. I can confirm that Ensign Tuvok and Lt. Uhura ARE two of the four personnel, and William T. Riker IS NOT one of them:<br>
<br>
<br>
Puzzle Number Two: Klingon Beat Up On<br>
<br>
DIFFICULTY: Question on the Academy Entrance Exam (Medium-Hard) <br>
CARD KNOWLEDGE <br>
<br>
<br>
Your Opponent <br>
<br>
Name: Pu Uoy Taeb <br>
Affiliation: Federation/Klingon/(Non-aligned) <br>
Rating: 1620 <br>
Deck Information: Seeds Treaty:Federation/Klingon with Open Diplomatic Relations <br>
Seeds all Federation facilities <br>
Does not use The Devil, personnel with CUNNING&lt;8, or Battle Bridge Door<br>
<br>
You <br>
<br>
Name: Loophole <br>
Affiliation: Federation/Klingon/(Non-aligned) <br>
Rating: 1572 <br>
Deck Information: Only Personnel and Ships in draw deck <br>
Seeds Treaty:Federation/Klingon with Open Diplomatic Relations <br>
Seeds and uses three side decks <br>
Do not use Storage Compartment Door or The Devil <br>
<br>
Current Situation: <br>
You have your only eight personnel alive on an undocked Yiridian Shuttle. Four of those personnel are Kor, Kang, Kolath, and Jadiza Dax so you can solve A Good Day to Live. Pu Uoy Teab has a Federation (with Captain Kirk) ship, three Klingon ships, and two Non-Aligned ships. *Each of your opponent&#146;s ships has WEAPONS=19* and can attack your Yridian Shuttle this turn (all staffed with a matching leader). You nor the opponent have no cards in hand, no events, hidden agendas, or incidents in play. Amazingly, you realize you are not doomed because you can use your personnel (and other special abilities) to prevent your opponent from attacking (or the increase your SHEILDS, etc.). Pu Uoy Taeb attacks you with every ship possible seperately, and your ship remains damaged on the table. **You were lucky!**<br>
<br>
Who are those four other people? <br>
<br>
Notes:<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
ANSWER TO PUZZLE THREE:<br>
<br>
Seed *Alter Records* (Bajor), *Cloaked Mission* (Romulus), and *two universal space* in addtion to three other missions at which you can seed three different non-Federation, non-Neutral Outpost. Which these missions, you can seed *Chamber of Ministers* and *Deep Space 9* at Bajor, *Office of the Proconsul* and *Continuing Committee* of Romulus, *Empok Nor* at one universal space, and *Neutral Outpost* at the other. Thus far, you have only used three missions. All these facilities allow Lore to report as a normal card play (if the Nors are commandeered and have Promenade Shops and a docking site). Since you have three mission slots left (and the opponent has all Gamma Quadrant missions), you can seed three non-Federation, non-Neutral outposts in order to have a ttoal of nine facilities where Lore can report as a normal card play. Deep Space Station K-7 is not on option because Lore can not report there as a normal card play.<br>
<br>
Puzzle Four: Perplexing Paradox, a LooPHolE<br>
<br>
Difficulty: A question to a question to a question to a question... (Hard)<br>
HISTORY OF RULES<br>
<br>
You: LooPHolE<br>
Rating: 1820<br>
Affiliation: LooPHolE<br>
Deck Information: A LooPHolE<br>
<br>
Your Opponent: LooPHolE II<br>
Rating: 1500<br>
Affiliation: Federation<br>
Deck Information: Yet Another LooPHolE<br>
<br>
The Current Situation:<br>
<br>
A long time ago, you lost to LooPHolE II; however, three months later, you beat LooPHolE II playing THE EXACT SAME GAME.<br>
<br>
What completes the paradox?<br>
<br>
Post Answer(s) when you rate this puzzle; answer(s) will be given in next puzzle.<br>
<br>
Questions?<br>
Dmial me.<br>
